&lt;p&gt;Hope School of Supernatural Ministry (HSSM) was started by Hope Auckland Christian Church in 2012 with the purpose of equipping people from Oceania in the Hope International Ministries (HIM) movement to become revivalists in their cities and their nations. We expected 20-25 students to attend but by the close of registration, we had almost 50 students. Because of God's favour and the wonderful feedback we received, we are running it again! In 2014, we will be opening the school (HSSM 1) to anyone who is hungry for revival in their city and we will be adding a follow-up school (HSSM 2) for students who graduated from the basic two-week school (2013 or 2014). There will also be an optional four-day mission trip to students who have attended HSSM 2.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Purpose&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our goal is to train up Sons and Daughters of God with a culture of revival and a lifestyle of the supernatural. There is a strong emphasis on healing, developing a prophetic culture, and demonstrating the gospel with power. At the end of the school, graduating students would carry Heaven's atmosphere back to their homes, churches and communities.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2&gt;Core values&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
We are committed to the truth that God is good, that He loves people and that He has given His Church supernatural power to bring individuals and cities into wholeness.&lt;/p&gt;
